news.title: Jobless claims tumble to 218,000, well below estimate despite fears of labor market weakness
news.summary: Initial claims for unemployment insurance were expected to total 235,000 for the week ending Sept. 20, according to the Labor Department. The U.S. unemployment rate is currently at 4.7 percent.

news.title: Starbucks to close stores, lay off workers in $1 billion restructuring plan
news.summary: Starbucks announced a $1 billion restructuring plan Thursday. It involves closing some of its North American coffeehouses and laying off about 900 workers.

news.title: Trump OMB orders preparation for mass firings of federal workers if government shuts down
news.summary: The warning could ratchet up pressure on Congress to strike a deal to avert a government shutdown. The warning comes as the U.S. faces a possible government shutdown on Friday.

news.title: Disney investors say handling of Jimmy Kimmel suspension put politics over shareholders, demand records
news.summary: Disney investors seek board materials, communications and policies related to the suspension of "Jimmy Kimmel Live!" A group of Disney investors are seeking board materials and communications.

news.title: Offshore driller Transocean plunges after offering shares at a discount
news.summary: Transocean has increased the size of the public offering, which closes Friday. Transocean: The public offering is expected to raise $1.2 billion.

news.title: I’m 70 and have Alzheimer’s. My son’s girlfriend put $750 worth of lottery tickets on a credit card I gave him. What can I do?
news.summary: “I contacted the credit-card company, but was advised they could not reimburse me for the theft,” she said. “I was advised that they could no longer reimburse me.”

news.title: Nvidia’s stock can soar 35% more, Barclays says. Why AI spending estimates now seem less ‘outlandish.’
news.summary: Barclays analysts see the AI infrastructure market reaching $2 trillion and beyond. The wave of AI data-center announcements in recent months has Barclays feeling more positive about Nvidia and other AI chip names.

news.title: Starbucks is cutting more jobs and closing stores as part of a $1 billion restructuring
news.summary: Most of the job cuts will be in non-retail positions, and many open positions will be closed. Starbucks is closing stores across the U.S. and Canada.

news.title: U.S. trade deficit sinks to 2-year low as businesses try to time orders to beat tariff price hikes
news.summary: The nation’s trade deficit in goods sank 17% in August to a two-year low. Businesses try to time imports and exports to pay the least amount of tariffs.
